# configuration

The default trade configuration for a given exchange (ex. binance) is loaded from config/defaults/binance.ini,
and saved in trader.ini if binance sections in trader.ini don't already exist.

# Trade modes

trade_mode realtime:
- In trade mode realtime, either captured or live websocket feed market data is processed to determine if a
given signal will 1) buy 2) sell 3) do nothing
- Setting rt_use_hourly_klines and rt_hourly_signal will allow limiting realtime trading by disabling or
enabling trading on a given trade symbol based on the rt_hourly_signal specified

